<section class="ww-section" id="about">
  <div class="ww-container ww-grid12">
    <div class="ww-eyebrow-row" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
      <span class="ww-eyebrow"><span class="ww-idx">01</span> &nbsp; About</span>
      <span class="ww-bar"></span>
      <span class="ww-eyebrow">Who is doing this, and why.</span>
    </div>

    <p class="ww-about__lede">
      Zak Winnick builds charging infrastructure for a living, and watches
      the wrong sites <em>quietly burn a million dollars apiece.</em>
      He's also been charging EVs for a decade across most of the major
      networks, and just started taking flight lessons. The channel is what
      happens when one person can't stop noticing things and decides to
      point a camera at them.
    </p>

    <aside class="ww-about__sidebar">
      <dl>
        <div>
          <dt>Day Job</dt>
          <dd>Founder and CEO, <em>Rangeway Energy</em></dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Community</dt>
          <dd>
            Community Director, <a href="https://bayarearivianclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bay Area Rivian Club</a>
            <br />
            Executive Director - <a href="https://norcalevs.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NorCal EVs</a>
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Podcast</dt>
          <dd>Host - <a href="#podcast">Ground Loop</a></dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Lives in</dt>
          <dd>Napa, CA</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </aside>

    <div class="ww-about__portrait">
      <img
        src="/images/zak-portrait.jpg"
        alt="Zak Winnick at Vasquez Rocks, R1T behind"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="1600"
        height="1200"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="ww-about__quote">
      <p>
        Most charging YouTubers test plugs. I test the parking lot, the
        lighting, the sign placement, the host's attitude. The plug is the
        easy part.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
